The Peoples Democratic Party, PDP, has commended the Edo State Governor, Godwin Obaseki for dumping the All Progressives Congress, APC. Obaseki had announced his resignation from APC during a chat with State House Correspondents at the Presidential Villa, Abuja. Reacting, PDP’s National Publicity Secretary, Kola Ologbondiyan described Obaseki’s decision as a bold and courageous move. Ologbondiyan said it was time for Nigerians to come together and save the country from the APC. In a series of tweets, Ologbondiyan wrote: “I just spoke with @GovernorObaseki. I commended his bold and courageous decision to abandon the fizzling Congress. “The time has come for all democrats to rally together and save our nation from the failures @OfficialAPCNg “A new life is brewing in Edo State @OfficialPDPNig as a major stakeholder is keenly following the development.#FizzlingAPC.”